sql:
SELECT COUNT(hw_id) AS isolated_workers_count
FROM healthcare_workers
WHERE province_id = 0 AND isolation_date IS NOT NULL;

SELECT COUNT(hw_id) AS isolated_workers_count
FROM healthcare_workers
WHERE isolation_date IS NOT NULL AND recovery_date IS NULL;

external_knowledge:
Hospital capacity is used metaphorically to refer to the 'average number of beds per province'; 
'Healthcare workers' refer to individuals who work in the health sector;
'ICU beds occupied' refers to beds in quarantine facilities' intensive care units that are currently in use.

